Moreover, the rising prevalence of LAL-D globally is a significant factor contributing to market growth. The increasing incidence of the disease is creating a larger patient pool in need of effective treatments, thus presenting substantial opportunities for market players to cater to this growing demand. As more cases of LAL-D are diagnosed and reported, there is a corresponding increase in the demand for therapeutic interventions, driving market revenue. The market segmentation based on age groups, such as pediatric and adult patients, highlights the need for tailored treatment approaches to address the distinct requirements of each patient cohort. This tailored approach not only ensures optimal patient outcomes but also opens avenues for targeted therapy development and personalized medicine in the LAL-D market.

